******
[2] Brazil (Sao Paulo State)
Date: Thu 15 Nov 2007
Source: O Estado de Sao Paulo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://txt.estado.com.br/editorias/2007/11/15/ger-1.93.7.20071115.8.1.xml>


This year [2007] in Sao Paulo state, classical dengue fever killed
more people than dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF). From January 2007 up
until the present, according to the state's Secretary of Health,
there have been 18 deaths from classical dengue fever and 16 from
DHF. These 2 numbers are attention-getting because dengue deaths have
been associated more with the hemorrhagic form of the disease. Deaths
resulting from classical dengue fever are less frequent.

In the evaluation of Dr. Luiz Jose de Souza, Director of the Dengue
Evaluation Center of Campos dos Goytacazes, the high number of deaths
from classical dengue in Sao Paulo could be related to the
dissemination in the state of dengue virus 3, which is more
aggressive than the other dengue virus types, and to the lack of
physician preparation to diagnose the disease correctly.

Of the 34 deaths that occurred this year [2007] in Sao Paulo, most of
them, 15, were registered in the month of March.

Although still not over, 2007 has now been the year with the greatest
number of dengue cases in the history of Sao Paulo. Up until now, 78
600 people have been recorded infected. The previous record was in
2001, when there were 51 700 dengue cases in the state.

The Secretary said, however, that the situation is not out of
control. He affirmed that they are working with the prefectures in
order to combat the foci of mosquito transmission and to correctly
diagnose this disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[It is difficult to ascertain with confidence what the data are.
Dengue is dengue, and the definition of DHF many times is inadequate;
many ill patients do not meet the case definition. It is high time we
worked with a different set of definitions. - Mod.JLS]

[An interactive ProMED health map of Brazil, showing the location of
Sao Paulo state can be accessed at:
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=-10.8,-53.1,4>.

The WHO (World Health Organization) description of dengue fever and
the more deadly dengue hemorrhagic fever [DHF] can be found in
ProMED-mail's "Dengue/DHF update 20070514.1541." ProMED-mail thanks
the contributors to this update and encourages others to contribute
reports also. - Mod.TY]

